20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20company%20released%20its%20quarterly%20results.%20In%20legally%20required%20disclosures%2C%20Microsoft%20included%20information%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-satya-nadella-openai-partnership-competition-collaboration-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eits%20relationship%20with%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20an%20investment%20in%20OpenAI%20Global%2C%20LLC%20(%26quot%3BOpenAI%26quot%3B)%20and%20have%20made%20total%20funding%20commitments%20of%20%2413%20billion%2C%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F789019%2F000095017024118967%2Fmsft-20240930.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESEC%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20investment%20is%20accounted%20for%20under%20the%20equity%20method%20of%20accounting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20previous%20SEC%20filings%2C%20Microsoft%20described%20the%20nature%20of%20its%20relationship%20with%20OpenAI%20as%20a%20partnership%20rather%20than%20an%20equity%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20long-term%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI%2C%20a%20leading%20AI%20research%20and%20deployment%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20wrote%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F789019%2F000095017024087843%2Fmsft-20240630.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20SEC%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20late%20July.%20%26quot%3BWe%20deploy%20OpenAI's%20models%20across%20our%20consumer%20and%20enterprise%20products.%20As%20OpenAI's%20exclusive%20cloud%20provider%2C%20Azure%20powers%20all%20of%20OpenAI's%20workloads.%20We%20have%20also%20increased%20our%20investments%20in%20the%20development%20and%20deployment%20of%20specialized%20supercomputing%20systems%20to%20accelerate%20OpenAI's%20research.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce75dcd2-7b31-4296-a5af-dd923cf8696e%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSoft%20money%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccounting%20expert%20Francine%20McKenna%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20new%20disclosure%20suggests%20that%20all%20or%20part%20of%20Microsoft's%20previous%20investments%20in%20OpenAI%20were%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20discounts%20or%20credits%20for%20services%20and%20internal%20spending%20that%20fell%20below%20a%20certain%20threshold%20where%20the%20software%20giant%20didn't%20need%20to%20publicly%20disclose%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20its%20partnership%20with%20and%20investments%20in%20OpenAI%20have%20not%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20October%2C%20OpenAI%20completed%20a%20%246.6%20billion%20funding%20round%20and%20Microsoft%20took%20part%20in%20that%20deal.%20OpenAI%20also%20began%20a%20process%20of%20changing%20from%20a%20mostly%20non-profit%20organization%20to%20a%20more%20traditional%20for-profit%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f340ea4-1398-4933-b292-46e87e27e201%5C%22%3ECrossing%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3Bthreshold%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft's%20new%20%26quot%3Bequity%20method%20investment%26quot%3B%20disclosure%20shows%20that%20the%20company's%20relationship%20with%20OpenAI%20has%20entered%20a%20new%20phase%2C%20at%20least%20from%20an%20accounting%20point%20of%20view%2C%20said%20McKenna%2C%20who%20writes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthedig.substack.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Dig%3C%2Fa%3E%20newsletter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20have%20had%20an%20equity%20investment%20before.%20But%20they%20did%20not%20disclose%20it%2C%20likely%20since%20it%20was%20probably%20soft%20money%20credits%20and%20minimal%20cash%20or%20none%2C%20so%20not%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20McKenna%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20latest%20round%2C%20it%20crossed%20a%20threshold.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20even%20started%20disclosi